### Requirements Met
- [x] Uses `github.com/go-webauthn/webauthn`
- [x] Supports platform authenticator (Touch ID, Windows Hello)
- [x] Supports roaming authenticator (YubiKey)
- [x] Resident key support (discoverable credentials)
- [x] Backup eligibility check
- [x] User verification: required for registration, preferred for login

## Next Steps
1. Run `go get github.com/go-webauthn/webauthn` in the API workspace to resolve dependencies.
2. Run migrations to create the new tables.
3. Install `@simplewebauthn/browser` in the web workspace for the client library.
4. Add frontend navigation link to `/settings/webauthn`.
5. Consider adding Redis-backed ephemeral session storage for production scale.
6. Add conditional UI mediation on the login page for auto-fill passkey prompts.
7. Implement credential metadata display (AAGUID lookup for authenticator names).
